# Azure App Registration Environment Variables for EduBuddyBridge
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual values

# Required: Your Azure App Registration Client ID
MICROSOFT_CLIENT_ID=your_application_client_id_here

# Required: Your Azure App Registration Client Secret
MICROSOFT_CLIENT_SECRET=your_client_secret_value_here

# Optional: Your Azure Tenant ID (defaults to 'common' for multi-tenant)
MICROSOFT_TENANT_ID=your_tenant_id_here

# Alternative: Use 'common' for multi-tenant scenarios (personal + organizational accounts)
# MICROSOFT_TENANT_ID=common

# ===== INSTRUCTIONS =====
# 1. Copy this file to .env: cp .env.template .env
# 2. Edit .env and replace the placeholder values with your actual Azure credentials
# 3. Add these same values to your Base44 dashboard or deployment environment
# 4. Run the test script to validate: ./scripts/test-azure-integration.sh
# 5. Never commit .env to version control (it's in .gitignore)

# ===== WHERE TO FIND THESE VALUES =====
# 1. Go to https://portal.azure.com
# 2. Navigate to Azure Active Directory > App registrations
# 3. Find your "EduBuddyBridge" app registration
# 4. MICROSOFT_CLIENT_ID: Overview tab > Application (client) ID
# 5. MICROSOFT_TENANT_ID: Overview tab > Directory (tenant) ID  
# 6. MICROSOFT_CLIENT_SECRET: Certificates & secrets tab > Create new secret

# ===== SECURITY NOTES =====
# - Keep these values secret and secure
# - Rotate the client secret every 12-24 months
# - Never share these credentials in emails, chat, or public repositories
# - Use different app registrations for development, staging, and production